text.tspan: Pelican Point appears to be providing sustained PFR
The unit first responds to frequency drop, then
ramps down to respond to over-frequency
Osborne per-unit power output drops down followed
by brief spike and return to dispatch. This suggests
power output affected by change in synchronous
North Brow, Hallett 1 and The Bluff rapidly reduce
output, with the latter two reducing to zero output
AEMO report said 4 wind farms in SA reduced
output to zero due to an incorrect protection
setting (same model). The Bluff appears to increase
output in stages despite over-frequency. Similarly,
Waterloo appears to decrease output in stages.
Other wind units with footroom do not appear
